awd_titl_txt: New Modes of Metallacycle and Carbene Reactivity
awd_abstract_narration: In this project supported by the Inorganic, Bioinorganic and                    Organometallic Chemistry Program, Joseph M. O'Connor of the                     University of California, San Diego will continue studies in                    the area of organometallic research at the interface of                         metallacycle and carbene chemistry. This research directly                      impinges on the role of metal carbenes in alkene metathesis,                    alkene and alkyne polymerization, cyclopropanation chemistry                    and an impressive array of synthetic organic methodology.                                                                                                       The proposed research has its focus on iridium, rhodium and                     cobalt compounds and the development of new carbene coupling                    reactions wherein ring-expanded metallacycles of the above                      metals and ultimately four- and five-membered carbocycles would                 be accessible. In addition to the synthetic studies, structural                 and mechanistic studies will also be carried out.
